To prevent Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) vulnerabilities, you should always sanitize user input before displaying it in web pages. One common approach is to encode the user input to ensure that any HTML tags or special characters are treated as plain text and not interpreted as code by the browser.

Here's an updated version of your code snippet with proper security measures in place:

